The Najadeae I have also done;
B74.08.01, pp. 215-19. but RBrs Caulinia spinulosa is a new genus of Hydrocharideae (Aschersonia),
Bentham (1863-78), vol. 7, p. 183, refers to Aschersonia as a new genus erected by M in B74.08.01, p. 219, but refers it to Halophila, to which M considered it to be close. Although in his comment M considered that Caulina spinulosa should be treated as a new genus, he did not give a name to it. In B89.12.03, p. 193, M attributes the combination to Ascherson (1875), p. 368. See also M to P. Ascherson, 6 October 1874 (in this edition as 74-10-06c). whereas also Enhalus is to be added to the Australian genera of that order.
